5010 struct ftrace_direct_func {
5011         struct list_head        next;
5012         unsigned long           addr;
5013         int                     count;
5014 };
5015 
5016 static LIST_HEAD(ftrace_direct_funcs);
5017 
5018 /**
5019  * ftrace_find_direct_func - test an address if it is a registered direct caller
5020  * @addr: The address of a registered direct caller
5021  *
5022  * This searches to see if a ftrace direct caller has been registered
5023  * at a specific address, and if so, it returns a descriptor for it.
5024  *
5025  * This can be used by architecture code to see if an address is
5026  * a direct caller (trampoline) attached to a fentry/mcount location.
5027  * This is useful for the function_graph tracer, as it may need to
5028  * do adjustments if it traced a location that also has a direct
5029  * trampoline attached to it.
5030  */
5031 struct ftrace_direct_func *ftrace_find_direct_func(unsigned long addr)
     /*   */
5032 {
5033         struct ftrace_direct_func *entry;
5034         bool found = false;
5035 
5036         /* May be called by fgraph trampoline (protected by rcu tasks) */
5037         list_for_each_entry_rcu(entry, &ftrace_direct_funcs, next) {
5038                 if (entry->addr == addr) {
5039                         found = true;
5040                         break;
5041                 }
5042         }
5043         if (found)
5044                 return entry;
5045 
5046         return NULL;
5047 }
5048 
5049 static struct ftrace_direct_func *ftrace_alloc_direct_func(unsigned long addr)
     /*   */
5050 {
5051         struct ftrace_direct_func *direct;
5052 
5053         direct = kmalloc(sizeof(*direct), GFP_KERNEL);
5054         if (!direct)
5055                 return NULL;
5056         direct->addr = addr;
5057         direct->count = 0;
5058         list_add_rcu(&direct->next, &ftrace_direct_funcs);
5059         ftrace_direct_func_count++;
5060         return direct;
5061 }
5062 
5063 /**
5064  * register_ftrace_direct - Call a custom trampoline directly
5065  * @ip: The address of the nop at the beginning of a function
5066  * @addr: The address of the trampoline to call at @ip
5067  *
5068  * This is used to connect a direct call from the nop location (@ip)
5069  * at the start of ftrace traced functions. The location that it calls
5070  * (@addr) must be able to handle a direct call, and save the parameters
5071  * of the function being traced, and restore them (or inject new ones
5072  * if needed), before returning.
5073  *
5074  * Returns:
5075  *  0 on success
5076  *  -EBUSY - Another direct function is already attached (there can be only one)
5077  *  -ENODEV - @ip does not point to a ftrace nop location (or not supported)
5078  *  -ENOMEM - There was an allocation failure.
5079  */
5080 int register_ftrace_direct(unsigned long ip, unsigned long addr)
     /*   */
5081 {
5082         struct ftrace_direct_func *direct;
5083         struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
5084         struct ftrace_hash *free_hash = NULL;
5085         struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
5086         int ret = -EBUSY;
5087 
5088         mutex_lock(&direct_mutex);
5089 
5090         /* See if there's a direct function at @ip already */
5091         if (ftrace_find_rec_direct(ip))
5092                 goto out_unlock;
5093 
5094         ret = -ENODEV;
5095         rec = lookup_rec(ip, ip);
5096         if (!rec)
5097                 goto out_unlock;
5098 
5099         /*
5100          * Check if the rec says it has a direct call but we didn't
5101          * find one earlier?
5102          */
5103         if (WARN_ON(rec->flags & FTRACE_FL_DIRECT))
5104                 goto out_unlock;
5105 
5106         /* Make sure the ip points to the exact record */
5107         if (ip != rec->ip) {
5108                 ip = rec->ip;
5109                 /* Need to check this ip for a direct. */
5110                 if (ftrace_find_rec_direct(ip))
5111                         goto out_unlock;
5112         }
5113 
5114         ret = -ENOMEM;
5115         if (ftrace_hash_empty(direct_functions) ||
5116             direct_functions->count > 2 * (1 << direct_functions->size_bits)) {
5117                 struct ftrace_hash *new_hash;
5118                 int size = ftrace_hash_empty(direct_functions) ? 0 :
5119                         direct_functions->count + 1;
5120 
5121                 if (size < 32)
5122                         size = 32;
5123 
5124                 new_hash = dup_hash(direct_functions, size);
5125                 if (!new_hash)
5126                         goto out_unlock;
5127 
5128                 free_hash = direct_functions;
5129                 direct_functions = new_hash;
5130         }
5131 
5132         entry = kmalloc(sizeof(*entry), GFP_KERNEL);
5133         if (!entry)
5134                 goto out_unlock;
5135 
5136         direct = ftrace_find_direct_func(addr);
5137         if (!direct) {
5138                 direct = ftrace_alloc_direct_func(addr);
5139                 if (!direct) {
5140                         kfree(entry);
5141                         goto out_unlock;
5142                 }
5143         }
5144 
5145         entry->ip = ip;
5146         entry->direct = addr;
5147         __add_hash_entry(direct_functions, entry);
5148 
5149         ret = ftrace_set_filter_ip(&direct_ops, ip, 0, 0);
5150         if (ret)
5151                 remove_hash_entry(direct_functions, entry);
5152 
5153         if (!ret && !(direct_ops.flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_ENABLED)) {
5154                 ret = register_ftrace_function(&direct_ops);
5155                 if (ret)
5156                         ftrace_set_filter_ip(&direct_ops, ip, 1, 0);
5157         }
5158 
5159         if (ret) {
5160                 kfree(entry);
5161                 if (!direct->count) {
5162                         list_del_rcu(&direct->next);
5163                         synchronize_rcu_tasks();
5164                         kfree(direct);
5165                         if (free_hash)
5166                                 free_ftrace_hash(free_hash);
5167                         free_hash = NULL;
5168                         ftrace_direct_func_count--;
5169                 }
5170         } else {
5171                 direct->count++;
5172         }
5173  out_unlock:
5174         mutex_unlock(&direct_mutex);
5175 
5176         if (free_hash) {
5177                 synchronize_rcu_tasks();
5178                 free_ftrace_hash(free_hash);
5179         }
5180 
5181         return ret;
5182 }
5183 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(register_ftrace_direct);
5184 
5185 static struct ftrace_func_entry *find_direct_entry(unsigned long *ip,
     /*   */
5186                                                    struct dyn_ftrace **recp)
5187 {
5188         struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
5189         struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
5190 
5191         rec = lookup_rec(*ip, *ip);
5192         if (!rec)
5193                 return NULL;
5194 
5195         entry = __ftrace_lookup_ip(direct_functions, rec->ip);
5196         if (!entry) {
5197                 WARN_ON(rec->flags & FTRACE_FL_DIRECT);
5198                 return NULL;
5199         }
5200 
5201         WARN_ON(!(rec->flags & FTRACE_FL_DIRECT));
5202 
5203         /* Passed in ip just needs to be on the call site */
5204         *ip = rec->ip;
5205 
5206         if (recp)
5207                 *recp = rec;
5208 
5209         return entry;
5210 }

5212 int unregister_ftrace_direct(unsigned long ip, unsigned long addr)
     /*   */
5213 {
5214         struct ftrace_direct_func *direct;
5215         struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
5216         int ret = -ENODEV;
5217 
5218         mutex_lock(&direct_mutex);
5219 
5220         entry = find_direct_entry(&ip, NULL);
5221         if (!entry)
5222                 goto out_unlock;
5223 
5224         if (direct_functions->count == 1)
5225                 unregister_ftrace_function(&direct_ops);
5226 
5227         ret = ftrace_set_filter_ip(&direct_ops, ip, 1, 0);
5228 
5229         WARN_ON(ret);
5230 
5231         remove_hash_entry(direct_functions, entry);
5232 
5233         direct = ftrace_find_direct_func(addr);
5234         if (!WARN_ON(!direct)) {
5235                 /* This is the good path (see the ! before WARN) */
5236                 direct->count--;
5237                 WARN_ON(direct->count < 0);
5238                 if (!direct->count) {
5239                         list_del_rcu(&direct->next);
5240                         synchronize_rcu_tasks();
5241                         kfree(direct);
5242                         kfree(entry);
5243                         ftrace_direct_func_count--;
5244                 }
5245         }
5246  out_unlock:
5247         mutex_unlock(&direct_mutex);
5248 
5249         return ret;
5250 }
5251 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(unregister_ftrace_direct);

5253 static struct ftrace_ops stub_ops = {
5254         .func           = ftrace_stub,
5255 };
5256 
5257 /**
5258  * ftrace_modify_direct_caller - modify ftrace nop directly
5259  * @entry: The ftrace hash entry of the direct helper for @rec
5260  * @rec: The record representing the function site to patch
5261  * @old_addr: The location that the site at @rec->ip currently calls
5262  * @new_addr: The location that the site at @rec->ip should call
5263  *
5264  * An architecture may overwrite this function to optimize the
5265  * changing of the direct callback on an ftrace nop location.
5266  * This is called with the ftrace_lock mutex held, and no other
5267  * ftrace callbacks are on the associated record (@rec). Thus,
5268  * it is safe to modify the ftrace record, where it should be
5269  * currently calling @old_addr directly, to call @new_addr.
5270  *
5271  * Safety checks should be made to make sure that the code at
5272  * @rec->ip is currently calling @old_addr. And this must
5273  * also update entry->direct to @new_addr.
5274  */
5275 int __weak ftrace_modify_direct_caller(struct ftrace_func_entry *entry,
     /*   */
5276                                        struct dyn_ftrace *rec,
5277                                        unsigned long old_addr,
5278                                        unsigned long new_addr)
5279 {
5280         unsigned long ip = rec->ip;
5281         int ret;
5282 
5283         /*
5284          * The ftrace_lock was used to determine if the record
5285          * had more than one registered user to it. If it did,
5286          * we needed to prevent that from changing to do the quick
5287          * switch. But if it did not (only a direct caller was attached)
5288          * then this function is called. But this function can deal
5289          * with attached callers to the rec that we care about, and
5290          * since this function uses standard ftrace calls that take
5291          * the ftrace_lock mutex, we need to release it.
5292          */
5293         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
5294 
5295         /*
5296          * By setting a stub function at the same address, we force
5297          * the code to call the iterator and the direct_ops helper.
5298          * This means that @ip does not call the direct call, and
5299          * we can simply modify it.
5300          */
5301         ret = ftrace_set_filter_ip(&stub_ops, ip, 0, 0);
5302         if (ret)
5303                 goto out_lock;
5304 
5305         ret = register_ftrace_function(&stub_ops);
5306         if (ret) {
5307                 ftrace_set_filter_ip(&stub_ops, ip, 1, 0);
5308                 goto out_lock;
5309         }
5310 
5311         entry->direct = new_addr;
5312 
5313         /*
5314          * By removing the stub, we put back the direct call, calling
5315          * the @new_addr.
5316          */
5317         unregister_ftrace_function(&stub_ops);
5318         ftrace_set_filter_ip(&stub_ops, ip, 1, 0);
5319 
5320  out_lock:
5321         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
5322 
5323         return ret;
5324 }
5325 
5326 /**
5327  * modify_ftrace_direct - Modify an existing direct call to call something else
5328  * @ip: The instruction pointer to modify
5329  * @old_addr: The address that the current @ip calls directly
5330  * @new_addr: The address that the @ip should call
5331  *
5332  * This modifies a ftrace direct caller at an instruction pointer without
5333  * having to disable it first. The direct call will switch over to the
5334  * @new_addr without missing anything.
5335  *
5336  * Returns: zero on success. Non zero on error, which includes:
5337  *  -ENODEV : the @ip given has no direct caller attached
5338  *  -EINVAL : the @old_addr does not match the current direct caller
5339  */
5340 int modify_ftrace_direct(unsigned long ip,
     /*   */
5341                          unsigned long old_addr, unsigned long new_addr)
5342 {
5343         struct ftrace_direct_func *direct, *new_direct = NULL;
5344         struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
5345         struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
5346         int ret = -ENODEV;
5347 
5348         mutex_lock(&direct_mutex);
5349 
5350         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
5351         entry = find_direct_entry(&ip, &rec);
5352         if (!entry)
5353                 goto out_unlock;
5354 
5355         ret = -EINVAL;
5356         if (entry->direct != old_addr)
5357                 goto out_unlock;
5358 
5359         direct = ftrace_find_direct_func(old_addr);
5360         if (WARN_ON(!direct))
5361                 goto out_unlock;
5362         if (direct->count > 1) {
5363                 ret = -ENOMEM;
5364                 new_direct = ftrace_alloc_direct_func(new_addr);
5365                 if (!new_direct)
5366                         goto out_unlock;
5367                 direct->count--;
5368                 new_direct->count++;
5369         } else {
5370                 direct->addr = new_addr;
5371         }
5372 
5373         /*
5374          * If there's no other ftrace callback on the rec->ip location,
5375          * then it can be changed directly by the architecture.
5376          * If there is another caller, then we just need to change the
5377          * direct caller helper to point to @new_addr.
5378          */
5379         if (ftrace_rec_count(rec) == 1) {
5380                 ret = ftrace_modify_direct_caller(entry, rec, old_addr, new_addr);
5381         } else {
5382                 entry->direct = new_addr;
5383                 ret = 0;
5384         }
5385 
5386         if (unlikely(ret && new_direct)) {
5387                 direct->count++;
5388                 list_del_rcu(&new_direct->next);
5389                 synchronize_rcu_tasks();
5390                 kfree(new_direct);
5391                 ftrace_direct_func_count--;
5392         }
5393 
5394  out_unlock:
5395         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
5396         mutex_unlock(&direct_mutex);
5397         return ret;
5398 }
5399 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(modify_ftrace_direct);
5400 #endif /* CONFIG_DYNAMIC_FTRACE_WITH_DIRECT_CALLS */

5618 int ftrace_regex_release(struct inode *inode, struct file *file)
     /*   */
5619 {
5620         struct seq_file *m = (struct seq_file *)file->private_data;
5621         struct ftrace_iterator *iter;
5622         struct ftrace_hash **orig_hash;
5623         struct trace_parser *parser;
5624         int filter_hash;
5625         int ret;
5626 
5627         if (file->f_mode & FMODE_READ) {
5628                 iter = m->private;
5629                 seq_release(inode, file);
5630         } else
5631                 iter = file->private_data;
5632 
5633         parser = &iter->parser;
5634         if (trace_parser_loaded(parser)) {
5635                 int enable = !(iter->flags & FTRACE_ITER_NOTRACE);
5636 
5637                 ftrace_process_regex(iter, parser->buffer,
5638                                      parser->idx, enable);
5639         }
5640 
5641         trace_parser_put(parser);
5642 
5643         mutex_lock(&iter->ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
5644 
5645         if (file->f_mode & FMODE_WRITE) {
5646                 filter_hash = !!(iter->flags & FTRACE_ITER_FILTER);
5647 
5648                 if (filter_hash) {
5649                         orig_hash = &iter->ops->func_hash->filter_hash;
5650                         if (iter->tr && !list_empty(&iter->tr->mod_trace))
5651                                 iter->hash->flags |= FTRACE_HASH_FL_MOD;
5652                 } else
5653                         orig_hash = &iter->ops->func_hash->notrace_hash;
5654 
5655                 mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
5656                 ret = ftrace_hash_move_and_update_ops(iter->ops, orig_hash,
5657                                                       iter->hash, filter_hash);
5658                 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
5659         } else {
5660                 /* For read only, the hash is the ops hash */
5661                 iter->hash = NULL;
5662         }
5663 
5664         mutex_unlock(&iter->ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
5665         free_ftrace_hash(iter->hash);
5666         if (iter->tr)
5667                 trace_array_put(iter->tr);
5668         kfree(iter);
5669 
5670         return 0;
5671 }

5710 enum graph_filter_type {

5712         GRAPH_FILTER_FUNCTION,

5717 struct ftrace_graph_data {
5718         struct ftrace_hash              *hash;
5719         struct ftrace_func_entry        *entry;
5720         int                             idx;   /* for hash table iteration */
5721         enum graph_filter_type          type;
5722         struct ftrace_hash              *new_hash;
5723         const struct seq_operations     *seq_ops;
5724         struct trace_parser             parser;

5727 static void *
5728 __g_next(struct seq_file *m, loff_t *pos)
     /*   */
5729 {
5730         struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd = m->private;
5731         struct ftrace_func_entry *entry = fgd->entry;
5732         struct hlist_head *head;
5733         int i, idx = fgd->idx;
5734 
5735         if (*pos >= fgd->hash->count)
5736                 return NULL;
5737 
5738         if (entry) {
5739                 hlist_for_each_entry_continue(entry, hlist) {
5740                         fgd->entry = entry;
5741                         return entry;
5742                 }
5743 
5744                 idx++;
5745         }
5746 
5747         for (i = idx; i < 1 << fgd->hash->size_bits; i++) {
5748                 head = &fgd->hash->buckets[i];
5749                 hlist_for_each_entry(entry, head, hlist) {
5750                         fgd->entry = entry;
5751                         fgd->idx = i;
5752                         return entry;
5753                 }
5754         }
5755         return NULL;
5756 }

     /*   */
5760 {
5761         (*pos)++;
5762         return __g_next(m, pos);
5763 }

5765 static void *g_start(struct seq_file *m, loff_t *pos)
     /*   */
5766 {
5767         struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd = m->private;
5768 
5769         mutex_lock(&graph_lock);
5770 
5771         if (fgd->type == GRAPH_FILTER_FUNCTION)
5772                 fgd->hash = rcu_dereference_protected(ftrace_graph_hash,
5773                                         lockdep_is_held(&graph_lock));
5774         else
5775                 fgd->hash = rcu_dereference_protected(ftrace_graph_notrace_hash,
5776                                         lockdep_is_held(&graph_lock));
5777 
5778         /* Nothing, tell g_show to print all functions are enabled */
5779         if (ftrace_hash_empty(fgd->hash) && !*pos)
5780                 return FTRACE_GRAPH_EMPTY;
5781 
5782         fgd->idx = 0;
5783         fgd->entry = NULL;
5784         return __g_next(m, pos);
5785 }
5786 
5787 static void g_stop(struct seq_file *m, void *p)
     /*   */
5788 {
5789         mutex_unlock(&graph_lock);
5790 }
5791 
5792 static int g_show(struct seq_file *m, void *v)
     /*   */
5793 {
5794         struct ftrace_func_entry *entry = v;
5795 
5796         if (!entry)
5797                 return 0;
5798 
5799         if (entry == FTRACE_GRAPH_EMPTY) {
5800                 struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd = m->private;
5801 
5802                 if (fgd->type == GRAPH_FILTER_FUNCTION)
5803                         seq_puts(m, "#### all functions enabled ####\n");
5804                 else
5805                         seq_puts(m, "#### no functions disabled ####\n");
5806                 return 0;
5807         }
5808 
5809         seq_printf(m, "%ps\n", (void *)entry->ip);
5810 
5811         return 0;
5812 }

5821 static int
5822 __ftrace_graph_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *file,
     /*   */
5823                     struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd)
5824 {
5825         int ret;
5826         struct ftrace_hash *new_hash = NULL;
5827 
5828         ret = security_locked_down(LOCKDOWN_TRACEFS);
5829         if (ret)
5830                 return ret;
5831 
5832         if (file->f_mode & FMODE_WRITE) {
5833                 const int size_bits = FTRACE_HASH_DEFAULT_BITS;
5834 
5835                 if (trace_parser_get_init(&fgd->parser, FTRACE_BUFF_MAX))
5836                         return -ENOMEM;
5837 
5838                 if (file->f_flags & O_TRUNC)
5839                         new_hash = alloc_ftrace_hash(size_bits);
5840                 else
5841                         new_hash = alloc_and_copy_ftrace_hash(size_bits,
5842                                                               fgd->hash);
5843                 if (!new_hash) {
5844                         ret = -ENOMEM;
5845                         goto out;
5846                 }
5847         }
5848 
5849         if (file->f_mode & FMODE_READ) {
5850                 ret = seq_open(file, &ftrace_graph_seq_ops);
5851                 if (!ret) {
5852                         struct seq_file *m = file->private_data;
5853                         m->private = fgd;
5854                 } else {
5855                         /* Failed */
5856                         free_ftrace_hash(new_hash);
5857                         new_hash = NULL;
5858                 }
5859         } else
5860                 file->private_data = fgd;
5861 
5862 out:
5863         if (ret < 0 && file->f_mode & FMODE_WRITE)
5864                 trace_parser_put(&fgd->parser);
5865 
5866         fgd->new_hash = new_hash;
5867 
5868         /*
5869          * All uses of fgd->hash must be taken with the graph_lock
5870          * held. The graph_lock is going to be released, so force
5871          * fgd->hash to be reinitialized when it is taken again.
5872          */
5873         fgd->hash = NULL;
5874 
5875         return ret;
5876 }

5878 static int
5879 ftrace_graph_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *file)
     /*   */
5880 {
5881         struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd;
5882         int ret;
5883 
5884         if (unlikely(ftrace_disabled))
5885                 return -ENODEV;
5886 
5887         fgd = kmalloc(sizeof(*fgd), GFP_KERNEL);
5888         if (fgd == NULL)
5889                 return -ENOMEM;
5890 
5891         mutex_lock(&graph_lock);
5892 
5893         fgd->hash = rcu_dereference_protected(ftrace_graph_hash,
5894                                         lockdep_is_held(&graph_lock));
5895         fgd->type = GRAPH_FILTER_FUNCTION;
5896         fgd->seq_ops = &ftrace_graph_seq_ops;
5897 
5898         ret = __ftrace_graph_open(inode, file, fgd);
5899         if (ret < 0)
5900                 kfree(fgd);
5901 
5902         mutex_unlock(&graph_lock);
5903         return ret;
5904 }

5933 
5934 static int
5935 ftrace_graph_release(struct inode *inode, struct file *file)
     /*   */
5936 {
5937         struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd;
5938         struct ftrace_hash *old_hash, *new_hash;
5939         struct trace_parser *parser;
5940         int ret = 0;
5941 
5942         if (file->f_mode & FMODE_READ) {
5943                 struct seq_file *m = file->private_data;
5944 
5945                 fgd = m->private;
5946                 seq_release(inode, file);
5947         } else {
5948                 fgd = file->private_data;
5949         }
5950 
5951 
5952         if (file->f_mode & FMODE_WRITE) {
5953 
5954                 parser = &fgd->parser;
5955 
5956                 if (trace_parser_loaded((parser))) {
5957                         ret = ftrace_graph_set_hash(fgd->new_hash,
5958                                                     parser->buffer);
5959                 }
5960 
5961                 trace_parser_put(parser);
5962 
5963                 new_hash = __ftrace_hash_move(fgd->new_hash);
5964                 if (!new_hash) {
5965                         ret = -ENOMEM;
5966                         goto out;
5967                 }
5968 
5969                 mutex_lock(&graph_lock);
5970 
5971                 if (fgd->type == GRAPH_FILTER_FUNCTION) {
5972                         old_hash = rcu_dereference_protected(ftrace_graph_hash,
5973                                         lockdep_is_held(&graph_lock));
5974                         rcu_assign_pointer(ftrace_graph_hash, new_hash);
5975                 } else {
5976                         old_hash = rcu_dereference_protected(ftrace_graph_notrace_hash,
5977                                         lockdep_is_held(&graph_lock));
5978                         rcu_assign_pointer(ftrace_graph_notrace_hash, new_hash);
5979                 }
5980 
5981                 mutex_unlock(&graph_lock);
5982 
5983                 /*
5984                  * We need to do a hard force of sched synchronization.
5985                  * This is because we use preempt_disable() to do RCU, but
5986                  * the function tracers can be called where RCU is not watching
5987                  * (like before user_exit()). We can not rely on the RCU
5988                  * infrastructure to do the synchronization, thus we must do it
5989                  * ourselves.
5990                  */
5991                 synchronize_rcu_tasks_rude();
5992 
5993                 free_ftrace_hash(old_hash);
5994         }
5995 
5996  out:
5997         free_ftrace_hash(fgd->new_hash);
5998         kfree(fgd);
5999 
6000         return ret;
6001 }
6002 
6003 static int
6004 ftrace_graph_set_hash(struct ftrace_hash *hash, char *buffer)
     /*   */
6005 {
6006         struct ftrace_glob func_g;
6007         struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
6008         struct ftrace_page *pg;
6009         struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
6010         int fail = 1;
6011         int not;
6012 
6013         /* decode regex */
6014         func_g.type = filter_parse_regex(buffer, strlen(buffer),
6015                                          &func_g.search, &not);
6016 
6017         func_g.len = strlen(func_g.search);
6018 
6019         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
6020 
6021         if (unlikely(ftrace_disabled)) {
6022                 mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6023                 return -ENODEV;
6024         }
6025 
6026         do_for_each_ftrace_rec(pg, rec) {
6027 
6028                 if (rec->flags & FTRACE_FL_DISABLED)
6029                         continue;
6030 
6031                 if (ftrace_match_record(rec, &func_g, NULL, 0)) {
6032                         entry = ftrace_lookup_ip(hash, rec->ip);
6033 
6034                         if (!not) {
6035                                 fail = 0;
6036 
6037                                 if (entry)
6038                                         continue;
6039                                 if (add_hash_entry(hash, rec->ip) < 0)
6040                                         goto out;
6041                         } else {
6042                                 if (entry) {
6043                                         free_hash_entry(hash, entry);
6044                                         fail = 0;
6045                                 }
6046                         }
6047                 }
6048         } while_for_each_ftrace_rec();
6049 out:
6050         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6051 
6052         if (fail)
6053                 return -EINVAL;
6054 
6055         return 0;
6056 }

6058 static ssize_t
6059 ftrace_graph_write(struct file *file, const char __user *ubuf,
     /*   */
6060                    size_t cnt, loff_t *ppos)
6061 {
6062         ssize_t read, ret = 0;
6063         struct ftrace_graph_data *fgd = file->private_data;
6064         struct trace_parser *parser;
6065 
6066         if (!cnt)
6067                 return 0;
6068 
6069         /* Read mode uses seq functions */
6070         if (file->f_mode & FMODE_READ) {
6071                 struct seq_file *m = file->private_data;
6072                 fgd = m->private;
6073         }
6074 
6075         parser = &fgd->parser;
6076 
6077         read = trace_get_user(parser, ubuf, cnt, ppos);
6078 
6079         if (read >= 0 && trace_parser_loaded(parser) &&
6080             !trace_parser_cont(parser)) {
6081 
6082                 ret = ftrace_graph_set_hash(fgd->new_hash,
6083                                             parser->buffer);
6084                 trace_parser_clear(parser);
6085         }
6086 
6087         if (!ret)
6088                 ret = read;
6089 
6090         return ret;
6091 }

6164 static int ftrace_cmp_ips(const void *a, const void *b)
     /*   */
6165 {
6166         const unsigned long *ipa = a;
6167         const unsigned long *ipb = b;
6168 
6169         if (*ipa > *ipb)
6170                 return 1;
6171         if (*ipa < *ipb)
6172                 return -1;
6173         return 0;
6174 }

6176 static int ftrace_process_locs(struct module *mod,
     /*   */
6177                                unsigned long *start,
6178                                unsigned long *end)
6179 {
6180         struct ftrace_page *start_pg;
6181         struct ftrace_page *pg;
6182         struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
6183         unsigned long count;
6184         unsigned long *p;
6185         unsigned long addr;
6186         unsigned long flags = 0; /* Shut up gcc */
6187         int ret = -ENOMEM;
6188 
6189         count = end - start;
6190 
6191         if (!count)
6192                 return 0;
6193 
6194         sort(start, count, sizeof(*start),
6195              ftrace_cmp_ips, NULL);
6196 
6197         start_pg = ftrace_allocate_pages(count);
6198         if (!start_pg)
6199                 return -ENOMEM;
6200 
6201         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
6202 
6203         /*
6204          * Core and each module needs their own pages, as
6205          * modules will free them when they are removed.
6206          * Force a new page to be allocated for modules.
6207          */
6208         if (!mod) {
6209                 WARN_ON(ftrace_pages || ftrace_pages_start);
6210                 /* First initialization */
6211                 ftrace_pages = ftrace_pages_start = start_pg;
6212         } else {
6213                 if (!ftrace_pages)
6214                         goto out;
6215 
6216                 if (WARN_ON(ftrace_pages->next)) {
6217                         /* Hmm, we have free pages? */
6218                         while (ftrace_pages->next)
6219                                 ftrace_pages = ftrace_pages->next;
6220                 }
6221 
6222                 ftrace_pages->next = start_pg;
6223         }
6224 
6225         p = start;
6226         pg = start_pg;
6227         while (p < end) {
6228                 addr = ftrace_call_adjust(*p++);
6229                 /*
6230                  * Some architecture linkers will pad between
6231                  * the different mcount_loc sections of different
6232                  * object files to satisfy alignments.
6233                  * Skip any NULL pointers.
6234                  */
6235                 if (!addr)
6236                         continue;
6237 
6238                 if (pg->index == pg->size) {
6239                         /* We should have allocated enough */
6240                         if (WARN_ON(!pg->next))
6241                                 break;
6242                         pg = pg->next;
6243                 }
6244 
6245                 rec = &pg->records[pg->index++];
6246                 rec->ip = addr;
6247         }
6248 
6249         /* We should have used all pages */
6250         WARN_ON(pg->next);
6251 
6252         /* Assign the last page to ftrace_pages */
6253         ftrace_pages = pg;
6254 
6255         /*
6256          * We only need to disable interrupts on start up
6257          * because we are modifying code that an interrupt
6258          * may execute, and the modification is not atomic.
6259          * But for modules, nothing runs the code we modify
6260          * until we are finished with it, and there's no
6261          * reason to cause large interrupt latencies while we do it.
6262          */
6263         if (!mod)
6264                 local_irq_save(flags);
6265         ftrace_update_code(mod, start_pg);
6266         if (!mod)
6267                 local_irq_restore(flags);
6268         ret = 0;
6269  out:
6270         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6271 
6272         return ret;
6273 }

     /*   */

6319 static int referenced_filters(struct dyn_ftrace *rec)
     /*   */
6320 {
6321         struct ftrace_ops *ops;
6322         int cnt = 0;
6323 
6324         for (ops = ftrace_ops_list; ops != &ftrace_list_end; ops = ops->next) {
6325                 if (ops_references_rec(ops, rec)) {
6326                         if (WARN_ON_ONCE(ops->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_DIRECT))
6327                                 continue;
6328                         if (WARN_ON_ONCE(ops->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_IPMODIFY))
6329                                 continue;
6330                         cnt++;
6331                         if (ops->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_SAVE_REGS)
6332                                 rec->flags |= FTRACE_FL_REGS;
6333                         if (cnt == 1 && ops->trampoline)
6334                                 rec->flags |= FTRACE_FL_TRAMP;
6335                         else
6336                                 rec->flags &= ~FTRACE_FL_TRAMP;
6337                 }
6338         }
6339 
6340         return cnt;
6341 }

6343 static void
6344 clear_mod_from_hash(struct ftrace_page *pg, struct ftrace_hash *hash)
     /*   */
6345 {
6346         struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
6347         struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
6348         int i;
6349 
6350         if (ftrace_hash_empty(hash))
6351                 return;
6352 
6353         for (i = 0; i < pg->index; i++) {
6354                 rec = &pg->records[i];
6355                 entry = __ftrace_lookup_ip(hash, rec->ip);
6356                 /*
6357                  * Do not allow this rec to match again.
6358                  * Yeah, it may waste some memory, but will be removed
6359                  * if/when the hash is modified again.
6360                  */
6361                 if (entry)
6362                         entry->ip = 0;
6363         }
6364 }

6367 static void clear_mod_from_hashes(struct ftrace_page *pg)
     /*   */
6368 {
6369         struct trace_array *tr;
6370 
6371         mutex_lock(&trace_types_lock);
6372         list_for_each_entry(tr, &ftrace_trace_arrays, list) {
6373                 if (!tr->ops || !tr->ops->func_hash)
6374                         continue;
6375                 mutex_lock(&tr->ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
6376                 clear_mod_from_hash(pg, tr->ops->func_hash->filter_hash);
6377                 clear_mod_from_hash(pg, tr->ops->func_hash->notrace_hash);
6378                 mutex_unlock(&tr->ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
6379         }
6380         mutex_unlock(&trace_types_lock);

6398 
6399 void ftrace_release_mod(struct module *mod)
     /*   */
6400 {
6401         struct ftrace_mod_map *mod_map;
6402         struct ftrace_mod_map *n;
6403         struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
6404         struct ftrace_page **last_pg;
6405         struct ftrace_page *tmp_page = NULL;
6406         struct ftrace_page *pg;
6407         int order;
6408 
6409         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
6410 
6411         if (ftrace_disabled)
6412                 goto out_unlock;
6413 
6414         list_for_each_entry_safe(mod_map, n, &ftrace_mod_maps, list) {
6415                 if (mod_map->mod == mod) {
6416                         list_del_rcu(&mod_map->list);
6417                         call_rcu(&mod_map->rcu, ftrace_free_mod_map);
6418                         break;
6419                 }
6420         }
6421 
6422         /*
6423          * Each module has its own ftrace_pages, remove
6424          * them from the list.
6425          */
6426         last_pg = &ftrace_pages_start;
6427         for (pg = ftrace_pages_start; pg; pg = *last_pg) {
6428                 rec = &pg->records[0];
6429                 if (within_module_core(rec->ip, mod) ||
6430                     within_module_init(rec->ip, mod)) {
6431                         /*
6432                          * As core pages are first, the first
6433                          * page should never be a module page.
6434                          */
6435                         if (WARN_ON(pg == ftrace_pages_start))
6436                                 goto out_unlock;
6437 
6438                         /* Check if we are deleting the last page */
6439                         if (pg == ftrace_pages)
6440                                 ftrace_pages = next_to_ftrace_page(last_pg);
6441 
6442                         ftrace_update_tot_cnt -= pg->index;
6443                         *last_pg = pg->next;
6444 
6445                         pg->next = tmp_page;
6446                         tmp_page = pg;
6447                 } else
6448                         last_pg = &pg->next;
6449         }
6450  out_unlock:
6451         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6452 
6453         for (pg = tmp_page; pg; pg = tmp_page) {
6454 
6455                 /* Needs to be called outside of ftrace_lock */
6456                 clear_mod_from_hashes(pg);
6457 
6458                 order = get_count_order(pg->size / ENTRIES_PER_PAGE);
6459                 if (order >= 0)
6460                         free_pages((unsigned long)pg->records, order);
6461                 tmp_page = pg->next;
6462                 kfree(pg);
6463                 ftrace_number_of_pages -= 1 << order;
6464                 ftrace_number_of_groups--;
6465         }
6466 }
6467 
6468 void ftrace_module_enable(struct module *mod)
     /*   */
6469 {
6470         struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
6471         struct ftrace_page *pg;
6472 
6473         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
6474 
6475         if (ftrace_disabled)
6476                 goto out_unlock;
6477 
6478         /*
6479          * If the tracing is enabled, go ahead and enable the record.
6480          *
6481          * The reason not to enable the record immediately is the
6482          * inherent check of ftrace_make_nop/ftrace_make_call for
6483          * correct previous instructions.  Making first the NOP
6484          * conversion puts the module to the correct state, thus
6485          * passing the ftrace_make_call check.
6486          *
6487          * We also delay this to after the module code already set the
6488          * text to read-only, as we now need to set it back to read-write
6489          * so that we can modify the text.
6490          */
6491         if (ftrace_start_up)
6492                 ftrace_arch_code_modify_prepare();
6493 
6494         do_for_each_ftrace_rec(pg, rec) {
6495                 int cnt;
6496                 /*
6497                  * do_for_each_ftrace_rec() is a double loop.
6498                  * module text shares the pg. If a record is
6499                  * not part of this module, then skip this pg,
6500                  * which the "break" will do.
6501                  */
6502                 if (!within_module_core(rec->ip, mod) &&
6503                     !within_module_init(rec->ip, mod))
6504                         break;
6505 
6506                 cnt = 0;
6507 
6508                 /*
6509                  * When adding a module, we need to check if tracers are
6510                  * currently enabled and if they are, and can trace this record,
6511                  * we need to enable the module functions as well as update the
6512                  * reference counts for those function records.
6513                  */
6514                 if (ftrace_start_up)
6515                         cnt += referenced_filters(rec);
6516 
6517                 rec->flags &= ~FTRACE_FL_DISABLED;
6518                 rec->flags += cnt;
6519 
6520                 if (ftrace_start_up && cnt) {
6521                         int failed = __ftrace_replace_code(rec, 1);
6522                         if (failed) {
6523                                 ftrace_bug(failed, rec);
6524                                 goto out_loop;
6525                         }
6526                 }
6527 
6528         } while_for_each_ftrace_rec();
6529 
6530  out_loop:
6531         if (ftrace_start_up)
6532                 ftrace_arch_code_modify_post_process();
6533 
6534  out_unlock:
6535         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6536 
6537         process_cached_mods(mod->name);
6538 }
6539 
6540 void ftrace_module_init(struct module *mod)
     /*   */
6541 {
6542         if (ftrace_disabled || !mod->num_ftrace_callsites)
6543                 return;
6544 
6545         ftrace_process_locs(mod, mod->ftrace_callsites,
6546                             mod->ftrace_callsites + mod->num_ftrace_callsites);
6547 }

6549 static void save_ftrace_mod_rec(struct ftrace_mod_map *mod_map,
     /*   */
6550                                 struct dyn_ftrace *rec)
6551 {
6552         struct ftrace_mod_func *mod_func;
6553         unsigned long symsize;
6554         unsigned long offset;
6555         char str[KSYM_SYMBOL_LEN];
6556         char *modname;
6557         const char *ret;
6558 
6559         ret = kallsyms_lookup(rec->ip, &symsize, &offset, &modname, str);
6560         if (!ret)
6561                 return;
6562 
6563         mod_func = kmalloc(sizeof(*mod_func), GFP_KERNEL);
6564         if (!mod_func)
6565                 return;
6566 
6567         mod_func->name = kstrdup(str, GFP_KERNEL);
6568         if (!mod_func->name) {
6569                 kfree(mod_func);
6570                 return;
6571         }
6572 
6573         mod_func->ip = rec->ip - offset;
6574         mod_func->size = symsize;
6575 
6576         mod_map->num_funcs++;
6577 
6578         list_add_rcu(&mod_func->list, &mod_map->funcs);
6579 }

6581 static struct ftrace_mod_map *
6582 allocate_ftrace_mod_map(struct module *mod,
     /*   */
6583                         unsigned long start, unsigned long end)
6584 {
6585         struct ftrace_mod_map *mod_map;
6586 
6587         mod_map = kmalloc(sizeof(*mod_map), GFP_KERNEL);
6588         if (!mod_map)
6589                 return NULL;
6590 
6591         mod_map->mod = mod;
6592         mod_map->start_addr = start;
6593         mod_map->end_addr = end;
6594         mod_map->num_funcs = 0;
6595 
6596         INIT_LIST_HEAD_RCU(&mod_map->funcs);
6597 
6598         list_add_rcu(&mod_map->list, &ftrace_mod_maps);

6600         return mod_map;

6603 static const char *
6604 ftrace_func_address_lookup(struct ftrace_mod_map *mod_map,
     /*   */
6605                            unsigned long addr, unsigned long *size,
6606                            unsigned long *off, char *sym)
6607 {
6608         struct ftrace_mod_func *found_func =  NULL;
6609         struct ftrace_mod_func *mod_func;
6610 
6611         list_for_each_entry_rcu(mod_func, &mod_map->funcs, list) {
6612                 if (addr >= mod_func->ip &&
6613                     addr < mod_func->ip + mod_func->size) {
6614                         found_func = mod_func;
6615                         break;
6616                 }
6617         }
6618 
6619         if (found_func) {
6620                 if (size)
6621                         *size = found_func->size;
6622                 if (off)
6623                         *off = addr - found_func->ip;
6624                 if (sym)
6625                         strlcpy(sym, found_func->name, KSYM_NAME_LEN);
6626 
6627                 return found_func->name;
6628         }
6629 
6630         return NULL;
6631 }

6633 const char *
6634 ftrace_mod_address_lookup(unsigned long addr, unsigned long *size,
     /*   */
6635                    unsigned long *off, char **modname, char *sym)
6636 {
6637         struct ftrace_mod_map *mod_map;
6638         const char *ret = NULL;
6639 
6640         /* mod_map is freed via call_rcu() */
6641         preempt_disable();
6642         list_for_each_entry_rcu(mod_map, &ftrace_mod_maps, list) {
6643                 ret = ftrace_func_address_lookup(mod_map, addr, size, off, sym);
6644                 if (ret) {
6645                         if (modname)
6646                                 *modname = mod_map->mod->name;
6647                         break;
6648                 }
6649         }
6650         preempt_enable();
6651 
6652         return ret;
6653 }

6655 int ftrace_mod_get_kallsym(unsigned int symnum, unsigned long *value,
     /*   */
6656                            char *type, char *name,
6657                            char *module_name, int *exported)
6658 {
6659         struct ftrace_mod_map *mod_map;
6660         struct ftrace_mod_func *mod_func;
6661         int ret;
6662 
6663         preempt_disable();
6664         list_for_each_entry_rcu(mod_map, &ftrace_mod_maps, list) {
6665 
6666                 if (symnum >= mod_map->num_funcs) {
6667                         symnum -= mod_map->num_funcs;
6668                         continue;
6669                 }
6670 
6671                 list_for_each_entry_rcu(mod_func, &mod_map->funcs, list) {
6672                         if (symnum > 1) {
6673                                 symnum--;
6674                                 continue;
6675                         }
6676 
6677                         *value = mod_func->ip;
6678                         *type = 'T';
6679                         strlcpy(name, mod_func->name, KSYM_NAME_LEN);
6680                         strlcpy(module_name, mod_map->mod->name, MODULE_NAME_LEN);
6681                         *exported = 1;
6682                         preempt_enable();
6683                         return 0;
6684                 }
6685                 WARN_ON(1);
6686                 break;
6687         }
6688         ret = ftrace_get_trampoline_kallsym(symnum, value, type, name,
6689                                             module_name, exported);
6690         preempt_enable();
6691         return ret;
6692 }

6717 struct ftrace_init_func {
6718         struct list_head list;
6719         unsigned long ip;
6720 };

6722 /* Clear any init ips from hashes */
6723 static void
6724 clear_func_from_hash(struct ftrace_init_func *func, struct ftrace_hash *hash)
     /*   */
6725 {
6726         struct ftrace_func_entry *entry;
6727 
6728         entry = ftrace_lookup_ip(hash, func->ip);
6729         /*
6730          * Do not allow this rec to match again.
6731          * Yeah, it may waste some memory, but will be removed
6732          * if/when the hash is modified again.
6733          */
6734         if (entry)
6735                 entry->ip = 0;
6736 }
6737 
6738 static void
6739 clear_func_from_hashes(struct ftrace_init_func *func)
     /*   */
6740 {
6741         struct trace_array *tr;
6742 
6743         mutex_lock(&trace_types_lock);
6744         list_for_each_entry(tr, &ftrace_trace_arrays, list) {
6745                 if (!tr->ops || !tr->ops->func_hash)
6746                         continue;
6747                 mutex_lock(&tr->ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
6748                 clear_func_from_hash(func, tr->ops->func_hash->filter_hash);
6749                 clear_func_from_hash(func, tr->ops->func_hash->notrace_hash);
6750                 mutex_unlock(&tr->ops->func_hash->regex_lock);
6751         }
6752         mutex_unlock(&trace_types_lock);
6753 }
6754 
6755 static void add_to_clear_hash_list(struct list_head *clear_list,
     /*   */
6756                                    struct dyn_ftrace *rec)
6757 {
6758         struct ftrace_init_func *func;
6759 
6760         func = kmalloc(sizeof(*func), GFP_KERNEL);
6761         if (!func) {
6762                 MEM_FAIL(1, "alloc failure, ftrace filter could be stale\n");
6763                 return;
6764         }
6765 
6766         func->ip = rec->ip;
6767         list_add(&func->list, clear_list);
6768 }

6770 void ftrace_free_mem(struct module *mod, void *start_ptr, void *end_ptr)
     /*   */
6771 {
6772         unsigned long start = (unsigned long)(start_ptr);
6773         unsigned long end = (unsigned long)(end_ptr);
6774         struct ftrace_page **last_pg = &ftrace_pages_start;
6775         struct ftrace_page *pg;
6776         struct dyn_ftrace *rec;
6777         struct dyn_ftrace key;
6778         struct ftrace_mod_map *mod_map = NULL;
6779         struct ftrace_init_func *func, *func_next;
6780         struct list_head clear_hash;
6781         int order;
6782 
6783         INIT_LIST_HEAD(&clear_hash);
6784 
6785         key.ip = start;
6786         key.flags = end;        /* overload flags, as it is unsigned long */
6787 
6788         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
6789 
6790         /*
6791          * If we are freeing module init memory, then check if
6792          * any tracer is active. If so, we need to save a mapping of
6793          * the module functions being freed with the address.
6794          */
6795         if (mod && ftrace_ops_list != &ftrace_list_end)
6796                 mod_map = allocate_ftrace_mod_map(mod, start, end);
6797 
6798         for (pg = ftrace_pages_start; pg; last_pg = &pg->next, pg = *last_pg) {
6799                 if (end < pg->records[0].ip ||
6800                     start >= (pg->records[pg->index - 1].ip + MCOUNT_INSN_SIZE))
6801                         continue;
6802  again:
6803                 rec = bsearch(&key, pg->records, pg->index,
6804                               sizeof(struct dyn_ftrace),
6805                               ftrace_cmp_recs);
6806                 if (!rec)
6807                         continue;
6808 
6809                 /* rec will be cleared from hashes after ftrace_lock unlock */
6810                 add_to_clear_hash_list(&clear_hash, rec);
6811 
6812                 if (mod_map)
6813                         save_ftrace_mod_rec(mod_map, rec);
6814 
6815                 pg->index--;
6816                 ftrace_update_tot_cnt--;
6817                 if (!pg->index) {
6818                         *last_pg = pg->next;
6819                         order = get_count_order(pg->size / ENTRIES_PER_PAGE);
6820                         if (order >= 0)
6821                                 free_pages((unsigned long)pg->records, order);
6822                         ftrace_number_of_pages -= 1 << order;
6823                         ftrace_number_of_groups--;
6824                         kfree(pg);
6825                         pg = container_of(last_pg, struct ftrace_page, next);
6826                         if (!(*last_pg))
6827                                 ftrace_pages = pg;
6828                         continue;
6829                 }
6830                 memmove(rec, rec + 1,
6831                         (pg->index - (rec - pg->records)) * sizeof(*rec));
6832                 /* More than one function may be in this block */
6833                 goto again;
6834         }
6835         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
6836 
6837         list_for_each_entry_safe(func, func_next, &clear_hash, list) {
6838                 clear_func_from_hashes(func);
6839                 kfree(func);
6840         }
6841 }
6842 
6843 void __init ftrace_free_init_mem(void)
     /*   */
6844 {
6845         void *start = (void *)(&__init_begin);
6846         void *end = (void *)(&__init_end);
6847 
6848         ftrace_free_mem(NULL, start, end);
6849 }

6851 void __init ftrace_init(void)
     /*   */
6852 {
6853         extern unsigned long __start_mcount_loc[];
6854         extern unsigned long __stop_mcount_loc[];
6855         unsigned long count, flags;
6856         int ret;
6857 
6858         local_irq_save(flags);
6859         ret = ftrace_dyn_arch_init();
6860         local_irq_restore(flags);
6861         if (ret)
6862                 goto failed;
6863 
6864         count = __stop_mcount_loc - __start_mcount_loc;
6865         if (!count) {
6866                 pr_info("ftrace: No functions to be traced?\n");
6867                 goto failed;
6868         }
6869 
6870         pr_info("ftrace: allocating %ld entries in %ld pages\n",
6871                 count, count / ENTRIES_PER_PAGE + 1);
6872 
6873         last_ftrace_enabled = ftrace_enabled = 1;
6874 
6875         ret = ftrace_process_locs(NULL,
6876                                   __start_mcount_loc,
6877                                   __stop_mcount_loc);
6878 
6879         pr_info("ftrace: allocated %ld pages with %ld groups\n",
6880                 ftrace_number_of_pages, ftrace_number_of_groups);
6881 
6882         set_ftrace_early_filters();
6883 
6884         return;
6885  failed:
6886         ftrace_disabled = 1;
6887 }

6975 static nokprobe_inline void
6976 __ftrace_ops_list_func(unsigned long ip, unsigned long parent_ip,
     /*   */
6977                        struct ftrace_ops *ignored, struct pt_regs *regs)
6978 {
6979         struct ftrace_ops *op;
6980         int bit;
6981 
6982         bit = trace_test_and_set_recursion(TRACE_LIST_START, TRACE_LIST_MAX);
6983         if (bit < 0)
6984                 return;
6985 
6986         /*
6987          * Some of the ops may be dynamically allocated,
6988          * they must be freed after a synchronize_rcu().
6989          */
6990         preempt_disable_notrace();
6991 
6992         do_for_each_ftrace_op(op, ftrace_ops_list) {
6993                 /* Stub functions don't need to be called nor tested */
6994                 if (op->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_STUB)
6995                         continue;
6996                 /*
6997                  * Check the following for each ops before calling their func:
6998                  *  if RCU flag is set, then rcu_is_watching() must be true
6999                  *  if PER_CPU is set, then ftrace_function_local_disable()
7000                  *                          must be false
7001                  *  Otherwise test if the ip matches the ops filter
7002                  *
7003                  * If any of the above fails then the op->func() is not executed.
7004                  */
7005                 if ((!(op->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_RCU) || rcu_is_watching()) &&
7006                     ftrace_ops_test(op, ip, regs)) {
7007                         if (FTRACE_WARN_ON(!op->func)) {
7008                                 pr_warn("op=%p %pS\n", op, op);
7009                                 goto out;
7010                         }
7011                         op->func(ip, parent_ip, op, regs);
7012                 }
7013         } while_for_each_ftrace_op(op);
7014 out:
7015         preempt_enable_notrace();
7016         trace_clear_recursion(bit);
7017 }
7018 
7019 /*
7020  * Some archs only support passing ip and parent_ip. Even though
7021  * the list function ignores the op parameter, we do not want any
7022  * C side effects, where a function is called without the caller
7023  * sending a third parameter.
7024  * Archs are to support both the regs and ftrace_ops at the same time.
7025  * If they support ftrace_ops, it is assumed they support regs.
7026  * If call backs want to use regs, they must either check for regs
7027  * being NULL, or CONFIG_DYNAMIC_FTRACE_WITH_REGS.
7028  * Note, CONFIG_DYNAMIC_FTRACE_WITH_REGS expects a full regs to be saved.
7029  * An architecture can pass partial regs with ftrace_ops and still
7030  * set the ARCH_SUPPORTS_FTRACE_OPS.
7031  */
7032 #if ARCH_SUPPORTS_FTRACE_OPS
7033 static void ftrace_ops_list_func(unsigned long ip, unsigned long parent_ip,
     /*   */
7034                                  struct ftrace_ops *op, struct pt_regs *regs)
7035 {
7036         __ftrace_ops_list_func(ip, parent_ip, NULL, regs);
7037 }
7038 NOKPROBE_SYMBOL(ftrace_ops_list_func);
7039 #else
7040 static void ftrace_ops_no_ops(unsigned long ip, unsigned long parent_ip)
     /*   */
7041 {
7042         __ftrace_ops_list_func(ip, parent_ip, NULL, NULL);
7043 }
7044 NOKPROBE_SYMBOL(ftrace_ops_no_ops);
7045 #endif
7046 
7047 /*
7048  * If there's only one function registered but it does not support
7049  * recursion, needs RCU protection and/or requires per cpu handling, then
7050  * this function will be called by the mcount trampoline.
7051  */
7052 static void ftrace_ops_assist_func(unsigned long ip, unsigned long parent_ip,
     /*   */
7053                                    struct ftrace_ops *op, struct pt_regs *regs)
7054 {
7055         int bit;
7056 
7057         bit = trace_test_and_set_recursion(TRACE_LIST_START, TRACE_LIST_MAX);
7058         if (bit < 0)
7059                 return;
7060 
7061         preempt_disable_notrace();
7062 
7063         if (!(op->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_RCU) || rcu_is_watching())
7064                 op->func(ip, parent_ip, op, regs);
7065 
7066         preempt_enable_notrace();
7067         trace_clear_recursion(bit);
7068 }
7069 NOKPROBE_SYMBOL(ftrace_ops_assist_func);
7070 
7071 /**
7072  * ftrace_ops_get_func - get the function a trampoline should call
7073  * @ops: the ops to get the function for
7074  *
7075  * Normally the mcount trampoline will call the ops->func, but there
7076  * are times that it should not. For example, if the ops does not
7077  * have its own recursion protection, then it should call the
7078  * ftrace_ops_assist_func() instead.
7079  *
7080  * Returns the function that the trampoline should call for @ops.
7081  */
7082 ftrace_func_t ftrace_ops_get_func(struct ftrace_ops *ops)
     /*   */
7083 {
7084         /*
7085          * If the function does not handle recursion, needs to be RCU safe,
7086          * or does per cpu logic, then we need to call the assist handler.
7087          */
7088         if (!(ops->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_RECURSION_SAFE) ||
7089             ops->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_RCU)
7090                 return ftrace_ops_assist_func;
7091 
7092         return ops->func;
7093 }
7094 
7095 static void
7096 ftrace_filter_pid_sched_switch_probe(void *data, bool preempt,
     /*   */
7097                     struct task_struct *prev, struct task_struct *next)
7098 {
7099         struct trace_array *tr = data;
7100         struct trace_pid_list *pid_list;
7101         struct trace_pid_list *no_pid_list;
7102 
7103         pid_list = rcu_dereference_sched(tr->function_pids);
7104         no_pid_list = rcu_dereference_sched(tr->function_no_pids);
7105 
7106         if (trace_ignore_this_task(pid_list, no_pid_list, next))
7107                 this_cpu_write(tr->array_buffer.data->ftrace_ignore_pid,
7108                                FTRACE_PID_IGNORE);
7109         else
7110                 this_cpu_write(tr->array_buffer.data->ftrace_ignore_pid,
7111                                next->pid);
7112 }
7113 
7114 static void
7115 ftrace_pid_follow_sched_process_fork(void *data,
     /*   */
7116                                      struct task_struct *self,
7117                                      struct task_struct *task)
7118 {
7119         struct trace_pid_list *pid_list;
7120         struct trace_array *tr = data;
7121 
7122         pid_list = rcu_dereference_sched(tr->function_pids);
7123         trace_filter_add_remove_task(pid_list, self, task);
7124 
7125         pid_list = rcu_dereference_sched(tr->function_no_pids);
7126         trace_filter_add_remove_task(pid_list, self, task);
7127 }
7128 
7129 static void
7130 ftrace_pid_follow_sched_process_exit(void *data, struct task_struct *task)
     /*   */
7131 {
7132         struct trace_pid_list *pid_list;
7133         struct trace_array *tr = data;
7134 
7135         pid_list = rcu_dereference_sched(tr->function_pids);
7136         trace_filter_add_remove_task(pid_list, NULL, task);
7137 
7138         pid_list = rcu_dereference_sched(tr->function_no_pids);
7139         trace_filter_add_remove_task(pid_list, NULL, task);
7140 }
7141 
7142 void ftrace_pid_follow_fork(struct trace_array *tr, bool enable)
     /*   */
7143 {
7144         if (enable) {
7145                 register_trace_sched_process_fork(ftrace_pid_follow_sched_process_fork,
7146                                                   tr);
7147                 register_trace_sched_process_free(ftrace_pid_follow_sched_process_exit,
7148                                                   tr);
7149         } else {
7150                 unregister_trace_sched_process_fork(ftrace_pid_follow_sched_process_fork,
7151                                                     tr);
7152                 unregister_trace_sched_process_free(ftrace_pid_follow_sched_process_exit,
7153                                                     tr);
7154         }
7155 }

7157 static void clear_ftrace_pids(struct trace_array *tr, int type)
     /*   */
7158 {
7159         struct trace_pid_list *pid_list;
7160         struct trace_pid_list *no_pid_list;
7161         int cpu;
7162 
7163         pid_list = rcu_dereference_protected(tr->function_pids,
7164                                              lockdep_is_held(&ftrace_lock));
7165         no_pid_list = rcu_dereference_protected(tr->function_no_pids,
7166                                                 lockdep_is_held(&ftrace_lock));
7167 
7168         /* Make sure there's something to do */
7169         if (!pid_type_enabled(type, pid_list, no_pid_list))
7170                 return;
7171 
7172         /* See if the pids still need to be checked after this */
7173         if (!still_need_pid_events(type, pid_list, no_pid_list)) {
7174                 unregister_trace_sched_switch(ftrace_filter_pid_sched_switch_probe, tr);
7175                 for_each_possible_cpu(cpu)
7176                         per_cpu_ptr(tr->array_buffer.data, cpu)->ftrace_ignore_pid = FTRACE_PID_TRACE;
7177         }
7178 
7179         if (type & TRACE_PIDS)
7180                 rcu_assign_pointer(tr->function_pids, NULL);
7181 
7182         if (type & TRACE_NO_PIDS)
7183                 rcu_assign_pointer(tr->function_no_pids, NULL);
7184 
7185         /* Wait till all users are no longer using pid filtering */
7186         synchronize_rcu();
7187 
7188         if ((type & TRACE_PIDS) && pid_list)
7189                 trace_free_pid_list(pid_list);
7190 
7191         if ((type & TRACE_NO_PIDS) && no_pid_list)
7192                 trace_free_pid_list(no_pid_list);
7193 }
7194 
7195 void ftrace_clear_pids(struct trace_array *tr)
     /*   */
7196 {
7197         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
7198 
7199         clear_ftrace_pids(tr, TRACE_PIDS | TRACE_NO_PIDS);
7200 
7201         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
7202 }
7203 
7204 static void ftrace_pid_reset(struct trace_array *tr, int type)
     /*   */
7205 {
7206         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
7207         clear_ftrace_pids(tr, type);
7208 
7209         ftrace_update_pid_func();
7210         ftrace_startup_all(0);
7211 
7212         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
7213 }

7218 static void *fpid_start(struct seq_file *m, loff_t *pos)
     /*   */
7219         __acquires(RCU)
7220 {
7221         struct trace_pid_list *pid_list;
7222         struct trace_array *tr = m->private;
7223 
7224         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
7225         rcu_read_lock_sched();
7226 
7227         pid_list = rcu_dereference_sched(tr->function_pids);
7228 
7229         if (!pid_list)
7230                 return !(*pos) ? FTRACE_NO_PIDS : NULL;
7231 
7232         return trace_pid_start(pid_list, pos);
7233 }

7235 static void *fpid_next(struct seq_file *m, void *v, loff_t *pos)
     /*   */
7236 {
7237         struct trace_array *tr = m->private;
7238         struct trace_pid_list *pid_list = rcu_dereference_sched(tr->function_pids);
7239 
7240         if (v == FTRACE_NO_PIDS) {
7241                 (*pos)++;
7242                 return NULL;
7243         }
7244         return trace_pid_next(pid_list, v, pos);
7245 }

7247 static void fpid_stop(struct seq_file *m, void *p)
     /*   */
7248         __releases(RCU)
7249 {
7250         rcu_read_unlock_sched();
7251         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
7252 }

7254 static int fpid_show(struct seq_file *m, void *v)
     /*   */
7255 {
7256         if (v == FTRACE_NO_PIDS) {
7257                 seq_puts(m, "no pid\n");
7258                 return 0;
7259         }
7260 
7261         return trace_pid_show(m, v);
7262 }

7307 static int pid_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *file, int type)
     /*   */
7308 {
7309         const struct seq_operations *seq_ops;
7310         struct trace_array *tr = inode->i_private;
7311         struct seq_file *m;
7312         int ret = 0;
7313 
7314         ret = tracing_check_open_get_tr(tr);
7315         if (ret)
7316                 return ret;
7317 
7318         if ((file->f_mode & FMODE_WRITE) &&
7319             (file->f_flags & O_TRUNC))
7320                 ftrace_pid_reset(tr, type);
7321 
7322         switch (type) {
7323         case TRACE_PIDS:
7324                 seq_ops = &ftrace_pid_sops;
7325                 break;
7326         case TRACE_NO_PIDS:
7327                 seq_ops = &ftrace_no_pid_sops;
7328                 break;
7329         default:
7330                 trace_array_put(tr);
7331                 WARN_ON_ONCE(1);
7332                 return -EINVAL;
7333         }
7334 
7335         ret = seq_open(file, seq_ops);
7336         if (ret < 0) {
7337                 trace_array_put(tr);
7338         } else {
7339                 m = file->private_data;
7340                 /* copy tr over to seq ops */
7341                 m->private = tr;
7342         }
7343 
7344         return ret;
7345 }

7347 static int
7348 ftrace_pid_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *file)
     /*   */
7349 {
7350         return pid_open(inode, file, TRACE_PIDS);
7351 }

7353 static int
7354 ftrace_no_pid_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *file)

7359 static void ignore_task_cpu(void *data)
     /*   */
7360 {
7361         struct trace_array *tr = data;
7362         struct trace_pid_list *pid_list;
7363         struct trace_pid_list *no_pid_list;
7364 
7365         /*
7366          * This function is called by on_each_cpu() while the
7367          * event_mutex is held.
7368          */
7369         pid_list = rcu_dereference_protected(tr->function_pids,
7370                                              mutex_is_locked(&ftrace_lock));
7371         no_pid_list = rcu_dereference_protected(tr->function_no_pids,
7372                                                 mutex_is_locked(&ftrace_lock));
7373 
7374         if (trace_ignore_this_task(pid_list, no_pid_list, current))
7375                 this_cpu_write(tr->array_buffer.data->ftrace_ignore_pid,
7376                                FTRACE_PID_IGNORE);
7377         else
7378                 this_cpu_write(tr->array_buffer.data->ftrace_ignore_pid,
7379                                current->pid);
7380 }

7382 static ssize_t
7383 pid_write(struct file *filp, const char __user *ubuf,
     /*   */
7384           size_t cnt, loff_t *ppos, int type)
7385 {
7386         struct seq_file *m = filp->private_data;
7387         struct trace_array *tr = m->private;
7388         struct trace_pid_list *filtered_pids;
7389         struct trace_pid_list *other_pids;
7390         struct trace_pid_list *pid_list;
7391         ssize_t ret;
7392 
7393         if (!cnt)
7394                 return 0;
7395 
7396         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
7397 
7398         switch (type) {
7399         case TRACE_PIDS:
7400                 filtered_pids = rcu_dereference_protected(tr->function_pids,
7401                                              lockdep_is_held(&ftrace_lock));
7402                 other_pids = rcu_dereference_protected(tr->function_no_pids,
7403                                              lockdep_is_held(&ftrace_lock));
7404                 break;
7405         case TRACE_NO_PIDS:
7406                 filtered_pids = rcu_dereference_protected(tr->function_no_pids,
7407                                              lockdep_is_held(&ftrace_lock));
7408                 other_pids = rcu_dereference_protected(tr->function_pids,
7409                                              lockdep_is_held(&ftrace_lock));
7410                 break;
7411         default:
7412                 ret = -EINVAL;
7413                 WARN_ON_ONCE(1);
7414                 goto out;
7415         }
7416 
7417         ret = trace_pid_write(filtered_pids, &pid_list, ubuf, cnt);
7418         if (ret < 0)
7419                 goto out;
7420 
7421         switch (type) {
7422         case TRACE_PIDS:
7423                 rcu_assign_pointer(tr->function_pids, pid_list);
7424                 break;
7425         case TRACE_NO_PIDS:
7426                 rcu_assign_pointer(tr->function_no_pids, pid_list);
7427                 break;
7428         }
7429 
7430 
7431         if (filtered_pids) {
7432                 synchronize_rcu();
7433                 trace_free_pid_list(filtered_pids);
7434         } else if (pid_list && !other_pids) {
7435                 /* Register a probe to set whether to ignore the tracing of a task */
7436                 register_trace_sched_switch(ftrace_filter_pid_sched_switch_probe, tr);
7437         }
7438 
7439         /*
7440          * Ignoring of pids is done at task switch. But we have to
7441          * check for those tasks that are currently running.
7442          * Always do this in case a pid was appended or removed.
7443          */
7444         on_each_cpu(ignore_task_cpu, tr, 1);
7445 
7446         ftrace_update_pid_func();
7447         ftrace_startup_all(0);
7448  out:
7449         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
7450 
7451         if (ret > 0)
7452                 *ppos += ret;
7453 
7454         return ret;
7455 }
7456 
7457 static ssize_t
7458 ftrace_pid_write(struct file *filp, const char __user *ubuf,
     /*   */
7459                  size_t cnt, loff_t *ppos)
7460 {
7461         return pid_write(filp, ubuf, cnt, ppos, TRACE_PIDS);
7462 }

7465 ftrace_no_pid_write(struct file *filp, const char __user *ubuf,
     /*   */

7517  *
7518  * This function should be used by panic code. It stops ftrace
7519  * but in a not so nice way. If you need to simply kill ftrace
7520  * from a non-atomic section, use ftrace_kill.

     /*   */

7527 }

7531  */

     /*   */
7533 {

7537 /**
7538  * register_ftrace_function - register a function for profiling
7539  * @ops - ops structure that holds the function for profiling.
7540  *
7541  * Register a function to be called by all functions in the
7542  * kernel.
7543  *
7544  * Note: @ops->func and all the functions it calls must be labeled
7545  *       with "notrace", otherwise it will go into a
7546  *       recursive loop.
7547  */
7548 int register_ftrace_function(struct ftrace_ops *ops)
     /*   */
7549 {
7550         int ret = -1;
7551 
7552         ftrace_ops_init(ops);
7553 
7554         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
7555 
7556         ret = ftrace_startup(ops, 0);
7557 
7558         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
7559 
7560         return ret;
7561 }
7562 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(register_ftrace_function);
7563 
7564 /**
7565  * unregister_ftrace_function - unregister a function for profiling.
7566  * @ops - ops structure that holds the function to unregister
7567  *
7568  * Unregister a function that was added to be called by ftrace profiling.
7569  */
7570 int unregister_ftrace_function(struct ftrace_ops *ops)
     /*   */
7571 {
7572         int ret;
7573 
7574         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
7575         ret = ftrace_shutdown(ops, 0);
7576         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
7577 
7578         return ret;
7579 }
7580 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(unregister_ftrace_function);
7581 
7582 static bool is_permanent_ops_registered(void)
     /*   */
7583 {
7584         struct ftrace_ops *op;
7585 
7586         do_for_each_ftrace_op(op, ftrace_ops_list) {
7587                 if (op->flags & FTRACE_OPS_FL_PERMANENT)
7588                         return true;
7589         } while_for_each_ftrace_op(op);
7590 
7591         return false;
7592 }
7593 
7594 int
7595 ftrace_enable_sysctl(struct ctl_table *table, int write,
     /*   */
7596                      void *buffer, size_t *lenp, loff_t *ppos)
7597 {
7598         int ret = -ENODEV;
7599 
7600         mutex_lock(&ftrace_lock);
7601 
7602         if (unlikely(ftrace_disabled))
7603                 goto out;
7604 
7605         ret = proc_dointvec(table, write, buffer, lenp, ppos);
7606 
7607         if (ret || !write || (last_ftrace_enabled == !!ftrace_enabled))
7608                 goto out;
7609 
7610         if (ftrace_enabled) {
7611 
7612                 /* we are starting ftrace again */
7613                 if (rcu_dereference_protected(ftrace_ops_list,
7614                         lockdep_is_held(&ftrace_lock)) != &ftrace_list_end)
7615                         update_ftrace_function();
7616 
7617                 ftrace_startup_sysctl();
7618 
7619         } else {
7620                 if (is_permanent_ops_registered()) {
7621                         ftrace_enabled = true;
7622                         ret = -EBUSY;
7623                         goto out;
7624                 }
7625 
7626                 /* stopping ftrace calls (just send to ftrace_stub) */
7627                 ftrace_trace_function = ftrace_stub;
7628 
7629                 ftrace_shutdown_sysctl();
7630         }
7631 
7632         last_ftrace_enabled = !!ftrace_enabled;
7633  out:
7634         mutex_unlock(&ftrace_lock);
7635         return ret;
7636 }
